meta {
  name: GET garage (vehicle list)
  type: http
  seq: 1
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/api/v2/garage?connectivityGenerations=MOD1&connectivityGenerations=MOD2&connectivityGenerations=MOD3&connectivityGenerations=MOD4
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
  User-Agent: vag-connect-ha-tests/1.17.3
}

docs {
  Lists VINs in the user's mysmob garage. Multi-key
  ``connectivityGenerations`` query parameter is REQUIRED for newer
  Skoda models (Kodiaq Mk2 / Enyaq 2024+ on MOD3/MOD4 connectivity).
  Without it the backend returns 403 Forbidden.

  Verified against ``skodaconnect/myskoda/rest_api.py::get_garage``.
  Implementation: SkodaClient.get_vehicles() in
  custom_components/vag_connect/cariad/api/skoda.py.

  See #75 (Kodiaq Mk2 403) for why this query is essential.
}
